author: Life in the 1800s
description:
My Patreon Page: https://www.patreon.com/c/Lifeinthe1800s

This video explores how other countries reacted to U.S. tariffs in the late 1800s, focusing on the global response to America's push for economic protectionism. As the United States raised import duties to protect its growing industries, major trade partners like Britain and Germany took notice—some retaliating with tariffs of their own, while others sought new markets. The video sheds light on the ripple effects of these policies and the role tariffs played in shaping international trade tensions during the Gilded Age.
title: How Countries Reacted To American Tariffs in the 1800s
